---
import DocLayout from "../../layouts/DocLayout.astro";
import MiniIndex from "../../components/MiniIndex.astro";

const start = [
  { href: "/docs/project-map.html", title: "Project map", description: "Core, Xilem, Comfy, Druid, and future front-ends." },
  { href: "/docs/current-facts.html", title: "Current facts", description: "Compact source of truth for humans and agents." },
  { href: "/docs/alpha-limits.html", title: "Alpha limits", description: "What is intentionally unstable before launch." },
  { href: "/docs/roadmap.html", title: "Roadmap", description: "Status lanes for documented, uncertain, future, and not-promised areas." },
];

const shared = [
  { href: "/docs/glossary.html", title: "Glossary", description: "UFO, GLIF, hyperbeziers, tracing, and project terms." },
  { href: "/docs/format.html", title: "Format notes", description: "UFO, GLIF, hyperbeziers, and compatibility." },
  { href: "/docs/troubleshooting.html", title: "Troubleshooting", description: "Alpha setup, UFO, tracing, and format checks." },
  { href: "/docs/support.html", title: "Support", description: "Where to file issues, discuss work, and send patches." },
  { href: "/docs/verification.html", title: "Verification", description: "Website checks, source checks, and current coverage limits." },
];

const xilem = [
  { href: "/docs/xilem.html", title: "Xilem overview", description: "Native desktop editor docs entry point." },
  { href: "/docs/install.html", title: "Xilem install", description: "Clone the source and open a UFO." },
  { href: "/docs/manual.html", title: "Xilem manual", description: "Tools, preview, selection, drawing, and transforms." },
  { href: "/docs/tracing.html", title: "Xilem tracing", description: "Import a bitmap, place it, trace or refit." },
  { href: "/docs/reference.html", title: "Xilem shortcuts", description: "Keyboard commands grouped for lookup." },
  { href: "/docs/source-map.html", title: "Xilem source map", description: "Where to look in the Runebender Xilem repository." },
  { href: "/docs/architecture.html", title: "Xilem architecture", description: "Application flow, state model, tools, data, and geometry boundaries." },
  { href: "/docs/capabilities.html", title: "Xilem capabilities", description: "Alpha matrix for running, editing, tracing, and formats." },
  { href: "/docs/examples.html", title: "Xilem examples", description: "Included UFO sources and what to inspect in each one." },
];

const otherPaths = [
  { href: "/docs/core.html", title: "Runebender Core", description: "Shared editing and data model foundation." },
  { href: "/docs/comfy.html", title: "Runebender Comfy", description: "ComfyUI graph and browser-hosted front-end path." },
  { href: "/docs/druid.html", title: "Runebender Druid", description: "Historical implementation and project lineage." },
  { href: "/docs/development.html", title: "Develop Runebender", description: "Contribution entry points across the project family." },
];

const taskPaths = [
  { href: "/docs/how-tos.html", title: "Task recipes", description: "Run with a file, trace locally, configure cloud trace, and inspect formats." },
  { href: "/docs/workflows.html", title: "Choose a path", description: "Start with a task and follow the shortest doc route." },
  { href: "/docs/tutorials.html", title: "Tutorial paths", description: "First run, editing, tracing, format, and contributor learning paths." },
];
---

<DocLayout
  title="Alpha docs."
  eyebrow="Documentation map"
  lede="This documentation separates shared Runebender concepts from editor-specific behavior. Start with the project map, then choose Core, Xilem, Comfy, or historical Druid depending on the work in front of you."
  status="Alpha documentation map"
  audience="Font tool users, contributors, agents"
  source="Website docs plus Runebender Core, Xilem, Comfy, and Druid repositories"
  stability="Structure is intentional; details may move"
  currentSlug="index"
  description="Runebender documentation map."
>
  <section class="doc-section">
    <h2>Start here</h2>
    <div>
      <p>Use these pages to understand the project family before choosing a specific editor path.</p>
      <MiniIndex items={start} />
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="doc-section">
    <h2>Shared concepts</h2>
    <div>
      <p>These pages are not owned by one front-end. They cover vocabulary, source formats, support, troubleshooting, and verification.</p>
      <MiniIndex items={shared} />
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="doc-section">
    <h2>Runebender Xilem</h2>
    <div>
      <p>The detailed manual pages currently describe the native Rust/Xilem editor. They are labeled as Xilem-specific so Comfy and future front-ends have room to grow separately.</p>
      <MiniIndex items={xilem} />
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="doc-section">
    <h2>Core, Comfy, Druid</h2>
    <div>
      <p>These pages reserve clear homes for the shared library, the ComfyUI front-end, project history, and contributor orientation.</p>
      <MiniIndex items={otherPaths} />
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="doc-section">
    <h2>Task paths</h2>
    <div>
      <p>Cross-document learning paths and recipes. These still lean Xilem-heavy where the detailed public docs are Xilem-specific, but the structure no longer assumes every front-end works the same way.</p>
      <MiniIndex items={taskPaths} />
    </div>
  </section>
</DocLayout>
